Kora Jazz Trio - Part 3
2008

When the Kora Jazz Trio released their two previous albums, the critics spoke of a 'delightful alchemy', of 'world jazz', or even 'a miracle of freshness'. A warm welcome for a musical fusion of a new kind that seemed yet so natural. The meeting between Mandingo tradition and the freedom of jazz. The combination of the Kora with West African percussions and Afro-Americon swing. The dialogue between the griot and the blue note.

